This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL) as it investigates the ability of recurrent neural networks to track abstract hierarchical syntactic structure in language processing tasks. It also uses language modeling as a training objective, which is a common approach in computational linguistics. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper includes an evaluation of model performance on nonsensical sentences, which could involve computer vision techniques for analyzing text and images (cs.CV).
